e. This opens the possibility to characterize the\ntemperature profile of the terminator region of hot Jupiters. Lastly, we found\nthat assuming a constant-with-altitude mixing ratio profile is a good\napproximation for most of the atmospheres under study.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 10 Oct 2016 11:07:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-12-21"}
